dinner_party:
I would choose the following figures for my dinner party: Winston Churchill, Marie Curie, Nikola Tesla, and Eleanor Roosevelt.

Winston Churchill for his strong leadership during challenging times;
Marie Curie for her groundbreaking scientific work and commitment to science despite significant adversity;
Nikola Tesla for his innovative vision and contribution to technology;
Eleanor Roosevelt for her dedication to social justice, human rights, and women's issues.

Imagine discussing their individual philosophies on life and work, their perspectives on current global issues, or how their experiences can inspire modern leaders and thinkers.
